Good first step.

I had to turn to the plotly book to get the animated lines correct <https://plotly-r.com/animating-views.html>.


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
sequence_counts |> 
  mutate(
    annotation = str_glue("W:{water}, L:{land}")
  ) -> 
  wl_annotate
```
:::

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
density_updates |> 
  plot_ly() |> 
  add_lines(
    x = ~prop,
    y = ~density,
    frame = ~seq,
    line = list(simplify = F, width = 3)
  ) |> 
  add_text(
    data = wl_annotate,
    text = ~annotation,
    frame = ~seq,
    x = 0.1,
    y = 0.025,
    textfont = list(size = 20)
  ) |>
  layout(
    showlegend = F
  )
```

